We have recommended that management direct the HRMO to execute contract for employees hired under JO to include statement of duties and responsibilities as a means by which their performance can be measured;

Submit the contract of services/job orders and Accomplishment Report for every paid payroll; and

Strictly observe Section 4 (6) of P.D. No. 1445 and COA Circular 2012-001 on government documentary requirements.

To thwart the happening of the above causes of untimely accomplishment of the LGU’s activities or to rectify, as a remedial measure on the noted deficiencies, we have recommended that management consider the following:

Direct the Municipal Engineer to prepare PERT-CPM on all projects implemented by administration to determine the work duration/period as a basis in enforcing the completion of the project; 

Direct the Municipal Engineer to prioritize and to fast tract the implementation of the LGU’s P/P/As;

Direct all officials and employees responsible for the conduct of procurement activity, including the end-users, to meticulously and judiciously plan the procurement in order to create an effective Annual Procurement Plan (APP); and

Direct the management to send a written demand to the supplier/contractor for the full and satisfactory performance of their obligations under their respective contract with the LGU and impose liquidated damages if necessary.

We have recommended that management require the concerned officers to submit all the required reports within the prescribed deadline and monitor compliance with the timely submission of reports;

Cause the suspension of payment of salaries of the concerned officials until they shall have complied with the requirements of the Commission in accordance with Section 122 of PD 1445; and

Hire a Municipal Accountant with appropriate qualification and fill up the other vacant position in the Accounting Office.

We have recommended to management to require the Accounting Section to maintain and update SLs showing detailed information of the cash advances granted, liquidations made, and unsettled balances for all accountable officers; and assign a regular personnel who shall be responsible for the review and analysis of the long outstanding and dormant cash advances; 

Make a formal request to COA for write-off of dormant unliquidated cash advances which remained non-moving for ten (10) years or more and where settlement could no longer be ascertained in accordance with COA Circular No. 2016-005 dated December 19, 2016; and

Strictly enforce compliance with COA Circular No. 97-002, on the granting, utilization and liquidation of cash advances to avoid accumulation of unsettled accounts as at year end.

